= Deleted Text

Deleted text is displayed with a strikethrough effect, useful for showing removed content.

== Basic Deleted Text

This paragraph contains [.line-through]#deleted text# within it.

== Deleted Text Examples

The old price was [.line-through]#$100#. The new price is $75.

The function [.line-through]#oldFunction()# has been replaced with newFunction().

== Deleted Text with Other Formatting

This paragraph has [.line-through]#deleted# and *bold* text.

This paragraph has [.line-through]#deleted# and _italic_ text.

== Deleted Text in Lists

* Item with [.line-through]#deleted# text
* Regular item
* Another item with [.line-through]#deleted# content

== Deleted Text with Links

The old link [.line-through]#https://old.example.com# has been replaced.

== Multiple Deleted Sections

This paragraph has [.line-through]#first deleted# and [.line-through]#second deleted# sections.

== Deleted Text in Code Context

The deprecated method [.line-through]#oldMethod()# should not be used.

Use `newMethod()` instead of [.line-through]#oldMethod()#.

